        "paragraph_index": 3,
        "text": "### Key Result\n\n**Ethylenediamine binds Ni²⁺ far more strongly than ammonia.** At 25 °C and zero ionic strength, the difference is:\n\n> **Δ log K₁ = 7.32 − 2.72 = 4.60 log units**\n\nThis means the Ni(en)²⁺ complex is roughly **40,000 times** more stable than Ni(NH₃)²⁺ (10⁴·⁶ ≈ 4 × 10⁴).",
